      1          /**
      2           *  @file		HeatMonitor.c
      3           *
      4           *  @brief		A monitor that checks the conditions to force the heater off.
      5           *
      6           *  @details    There are several requirements that require the heater's deactivation to prevent damages.
      7           *  			This monitor evaluates the required conditions and, if any of them is satisfied, forces the heater off, with a
      8           *  			higher priority than the Heat and Loads Control processes.
      9           *  			It has to be called as a POST MONITOR, so that it has all the updated information on the state requested for the
     10           *  			heater by the processes, and after WashHeaterFaultMonitor__Execution(), so that it has the updated information
     11           *  			on the heater being disabled due to a fault.
     12           *
     13           *
     14           *  @copyright  Copyright 2017-$Date$. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     15           */
